        "title": "feat(ui): per-agent ElevenLabs Voice/TTS settings in control-ui",
        "body": "## feat(ui): per-agent ElevenLabs Voice/TTS settings in control-ui\n\nAdds a Voice/TTS card to the control-ui agent overview panel, enabling per-agent ElevenLabs voice configuration directly in the UI.\n\n### Features\n- **Enable TTS toggle** — reflects resolved `auto` mode (`always`/`off`/`session`) with fallback to deprecated `enabled` boolean\n- **Provider dropdown** — Inherit default / ElevenLabs / OpenAI / Microsoft\n- **ElevenLabs fields** (API key, Voice ID, Model) — only rendered when resolved provider is `elevenlabs`\n- **SecretRef support** — API keys backed by SecretRef render as read-only \"•••••••• (SecretRef)\"\n- **Deep-merge config** — mirrors runtime `resolveEffectiveTtsConfig` contract (`messages.tts` base + `agents.list[].tts` override)\n- **i18n** — all voice/TTS strings wired through `t()` across 19 locales\n- **CSS** — toggle switch component styles\n\n### ClawSweeper P1 fixes (commit 34a54fd)\n- **`.deployed-commit` untracked** — removed from branch via `git rm --cached` + `.gitignore`\n- **ElevenLabs field gating** — fields now only render when resolved provider === `\"elevenlabs\"` (removed fallback that showed fields when provider was unset + TTS enabled)\n- **Test coverage added:**\n  - Non-ElevenLabs provider (openai) does not render ElevenLabs fields\n  - Unset provider with TTS enabled does not render ElevenLabs fields\n\n### Test coverage (14 agent tests, all passing)\n- Renders ElevenLabs fields when provider is elevenlabs\n- SecretRef API key rendered as read-only\n- Deep-merge inherited provider config\n- Auto mode reflected in toggle (always → on)\n- Non-ElevenLabs provider does not render fields\n- Unset provider + TTS enabled does not render fields\n\n### Build\n- 924 modules, 0 errors\n- i18n structural alignment: 11/11 pass across 19 locales\n- Deployed to local control-ui dist for manual verification",
